sales increased 41%, 40%, and 28% in 2011, 2010, and 2009. changes in currency exchange rates positively
(negatively) affected net sales by $1.1 billion, $(86) million, and $(182) million for 2011, 2010, and 2009. for a discussion of the effect on sales growth of exchange rates, see effect of exchange rates below.
the north america sales growth rate was 43%, 46%, and 25% in 2011, 2010, and 2009. the sales growth in each year primarily reflects
increased unit sales. increased unit sales were driven largely by our continued efforts to reduce prices for our customers, including from our shipping offers, by a larger base of sales in faster growing categories such as electronics and other
general merchandise, by increased in-stock inventory availability, and by increased selection of product offerings. additionally, north america sales growth reflects increased aws activity.
