the international sales growth rate was 38%, 33%, and 31% in 2011, 2010, and 2009. the
sales growth in each year primarily reflects increased unit sales. increased unit sales were driven largely by our continued efforts to reduce prices for our customers, including from our shipping offers, by a larger base of sales in faster growing
categories such as electronics and other general merchandise, by increased in-stock inventory availability, and by increased selection of product offerings. additionally, changes in currency exchange rates positively (negatively) affected
international net sales by $1.1 billion, $(107) million, and $(174) million in 2011, 2010, and 2009. we expect that, over time, our international segment will represent 50% or more of our consolidated net sales.
