and method for displaying and manipulating multiple calendars on a personal digital assistant (u.s. patent no.6,466,236). in december 2011, we entered into a settlement of the litigation that included, among other things, a payment to
the plaintiff and a non-exclusive patent license agreement. the settlement was not material to either the current or future years.  we cannot predict the impact (if any) that any of the matters described above may have on our business, results of operations, financial position, or cash flows. because of the inherent uncertainties of
